If soon-to-be Paramount CEO David Ellison is to be believed, one of the oldest companies in Hollywood is about to morph into a one-of-a-kind tech-media hybrid.&nbsp;
“It is essential for Paramount to be able to expand its technological prowess to be both a media and technology enterprise,” the executive said on an investor call last week, unveiling his plans for the long-anticipated merger of Paramount and Ellison’s Skydance Media.&nbsp;
Key to that expansion, he added, will be an effort to “rebuild” the company’s flagship SVOD, Paramount+, presumably utilizing tech and techniques drawn from his father Larry’s tech giant Oracle.

